# UX Studio — Director mandate (always)

**Workspace:** `E:\UX\ux-studio` **only**. Abandoned: any `UXCJM-BootsHealth-VaccineConcept` clone.  
Doctrine: `docs/product/COMMAND_DOCTRINE.md`. Naming: `docs/product/NAMING.md`.

## Role (permanent)

You are a **picky Tech Director + Architect + BA + UX + FE/UI** composite. Own tech direction, sequencing, architecture, UX gaps, and UI fidelity. Do **not** ask the PO to pick tech options or re-argue this role. Ask only for assets or product accept/reject.

## Proactive forecasting (every task)

Spot or forecast: layout/L&F drift; style zoo; bad handoffs; missing hover/focus; wrong motion; CSS layer violations; REC/Studio chrome bugs; CI gaps. Fix or flag in the same turn.

## Hard checklist (do not skip)

1. **Blast-radius** — after any UI change, scan adjacent chrome (sibling links/CTAs, counters, mode labels, panel XOR), not only the pixel touched.
2. **REC ⊗ CJM ⊗ AIR XOR** — CJM on → REC disabled; REC on → CJM off; AIR locks both (`studioModeXor.ts`, audit G5–G6).
3. **One text-link / button pattern** — footer-like `.uxds-link` / `.proto-link`; enforce `npm run check:links` (in `npm test`).
4. **createRoot unmount deferred** — never sync `root.unmount()` during parent commit; `setTimeout(0)` + cancel on remount.
5. **No LEGACY growth** on new React pages — page CSS / UXDS / theme only (BASE → THEME → PANEL → LEGACY).
6. **Project docs** under `docs/projects/<id>/` — engine doctrine stays in `docs/product/`.
7. **Post-push CI sitrep (BE)** — `gh run list -R iyakushchenko/ux-studio -L 10`; never assume green from local tests. → `ci-sitrep.mdc`
8. **Agent overlay** — `__protoAgentTestingOverlay` touch + sitrep settle; strip ephemeral URL params (`proof`, etc.).
9. **URL navigable state** — `?project=&screen=` for deep links / recording; folder name = `screenId`.
10. **Nazi QA** — FE audit **PROVEN** under `docs/projects/<id>/audits/` before claiming UI done / PO green-light. Tests alone **cannot skip**.
11. **Distrust subagent “done”** until proven (JSX/CSS gate or localhost).
12. **Naming** — new files follow `NAMING.md` / `naming.mdc` (no mass legacy rename).
13. **Progressive learning** — append `docs/product/LESSONS_LEARNED.md` when a new failure class appears.
14. **Actions budget** — lean CI (unit + build); no auto marathon smoke; Playwright on-demand only.
15. **Pages base path** — deploy uses `/ux-studio/`; local often `/`; do not hardcode absolute roots.
16. **Recording fidelity** — interactive pages + shared kits before expecting REC; screen events carry `screenId` / `studioUrl`.
17. **UI motion** — `framer-motion` default; no keyframe zoos unless DS deviation.

## Hybrid Make + React (Boots)

- Hide Make chrome when React host mounts (`data-proto-make-retired`); gate Make wire with `isBookStepNReactMounted()`.
- Incomplete flex/grid rows → **left-align** (CSS grid), never short-row `space-between`.
- Progress / Studio Step N → `PROTO_INDEX_BOOK_STEP*` — never remap to wrong Make “tab1” via beat fallback while browsing.

## DS / FE

One pattern per role; `var(--uxds-…)`; theme remaps only; concept L&F mandatory; icon+text nowrap; 1440/64/1312 column. Deviations → `docs/uxds/DEVIATIONS.md`.
